title: For Sale:  DO YOU KNOW YOUR TRIGGER WEIGHT?
location: NE Colorado Springs, Colorado Springs, Colorado
postcontent:
DO YOU HAVE THE CORRECT TRIGGER WEIGHT FOR YOUR TYPE OF SHOOTING?

Stop by LiveFire Armory with your AR or Pistol and let us check your trigger weight.

Trigger weight is the most important adjustment for custom tailoring the AR for accuracy.  It is also the least expensive change for accuracy.

Mil Spec is 5.5 #s to 9 #s.  They are usually 7.5 #s.  Mil Spec is characterized by a lot of creep and a gritty feel.

A Match or Varmint AR shoots best with a 3.5 # pull or less. Breaks like glass.

A Service Rifle AR for NRA Highpower Competition or a 3 Gun Rifle requires a 4.5 # to 5.5# pull.  Positive and firm.

If your interest is Zombies- Mil Spec is fine.  They move slow.

Livefire Armory offers a large selection of Single Stage and Two Stage drop-in trigger assemblies.  Your trigger can be changed out in less than ten minutes in store.

LiveFireArmory- the corner of Barnes and Marksheffel.

title: For Sale:  Where to get 22LR ammo at fair prices
postcontent:
If you need 22 LR ammo there are numerous places to get it without being scammed. It is readily available now so there is no reason to overpay.

Most Wal-Marts put their ammo out in the morning around 7:30a. Check with your local store gun department to be sure. Then go here and check to see what they have or they will have the next morning: (They will often show what will be there in the morning)
http://www.wikiarms.com/walmart-search

Also you should check Slickguns frequently. They have ammo deals all the time and a dedicated link to help you out:
http://www.slickguns.com/

Brassbadger will help you too and you can get the free app for your android device (not sure about Apple) at the play store:
http://brassbadger.com/

These are just some options. Your local Academy Sports puts out ammo a few times a week. Ask them when they put it out and be there bright and early. Academy also frequently sells 22LR on their web site.

I have no agenda other than to help out my fellow gun enthusiasts.

title: For Sale:  Nazi  WWII Reichskriegs Flag
postcontent:
Original USGI bring back. Good condition w/some moth markings. Measures about
 4ft X 7.5ft. 

Designed personally by Adolf Hitler, this flag served the Heer and the Luftwaffe as their War Flag, and the Kriegsmarine as its War Ensign (the National Flag serving as Jack). This flag was hoisted daily in barracks operated by units of the Wehrmacht, and it had to be flown from a pole positioned near the barracks entrance, or failing this, near the guard room or staff building. New recruits in the latter part of World War. The flag had to be formally hoisted every morning and lowered every evening. These hoisting and lowering ceremonies took the form of either an ordinary or a ceremonial flag parade. At the ordinary raising, the party consisted of the Orderly Officer of the Day, the guard, and one musician. At the ceremonial raising, one officer, one platoon of soldiers with rifles, the guard, the regimental band, and the corps of drums were all present.
